{"_id":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","name":"Dark Presence","type":"Folder","folder":null,"sorting":"a","sort":100000,"color":"#b10d18","flags":{"broken-tales":{"folderKey":"dark-presence","translations":{}}}}
{"_id":"2QX6fhyUVXUj4t5P","name":"White Rose and Red Rose","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"cJ7mogcelzhvkQXH","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hunt monsters and I have learned every bit \nof knowledge relevant to the fight against darkness. I am the \nmind that uncovers evil and my sister is the arm that punishes it.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 18","positive":"I hunt monsters and I have learned every bit \nof knowledge relevant to the fight against darkness. I am the \nmind that uncovers evil and my sister is the arm that punishes it.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ug12kTAJbpQbQfG6","name":"Gift - The Mind","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>White Rose is immune to any kind of \nmind control or fear effect, even if it is magical in origin. \nThrough her words, White Rose can interrupt mind control \nand fear effects on other targets. These effects end automatically on White Rose, while for other targets a Hunter is \nforced to make a Defense Check to keep their power active. \nRed Rose</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 18","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8DgslbVOSNi7NHHt","name":"Gift - The Arm","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Red Rose increases her OL by 1 when she \nattacks a Broken Tale with the specific purpose of killing \nthem.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 18","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pz1F2Xal1fqkG3Um","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>White Rose and Red Rose\nInspired by Snow-White and Rose-Red (Opponents)\nOnce upon a time, there was a poor widow who had two \ngood and hardworking daughters. White Rose and Red Rose \nwere the girls’ names. Both had a strict religious upbringing, following their Mother’s unwavering faith. The two \nsisters often played in the woods near the house, but \ntheir Mother feared nothing, convinced that her prayers \nmade the whole family immune to any misfortune. \nOne day, a strange talking Bear appeared at their door \nand told them that he was a prince cursed by an evil \nwitch. The woman and her daughters made the \nBear comfortable by offering him shelter. They \nfed him and kept him warm, and when he \nfell asleep, they mercilessly slit his throat. A \ntalking animal was surely the work of the \ndevil and as such had to be eliminated. A \nshort time later, a well-dressed Dwarf appeared at the house. He was looking for the \nprince he served, who had been cursed \nby an evil witch who had turned him \ninto a Bear. As a reward for finding \nhis master, the Dwarf offered a \nbag full of magical treasures. The \nwoman and her two daughters \nmade the Dwarf comfortable \nin the house, and they set \nabout sewing the cloak \nthat had been torn\n18\nfrom him on his journey. While the Mother prepared needle and thread, White Rose held the Dwarf down and Red \nRose thrust the scissors into his eyes. Blind and frightened, \nthe Dwarf tried to flee, but White Rose finished him off with \na deft blow. The offering of magical treasures was surely the \nwork of the devil, and once again the two young girls had \ncarried out God’s word as their Mother had intended. As the \nyears passed, the two girls became women. When their Mother ascended to heaven, she left her beloved daughters with \none last task: to find the devil in the world and put an end to \nhim, just as divine will dictates.\nWhite Rose\nDescriptor: I hunt monsters and I have learned every bit \nof knowledge relevant to the fight against darkness. I am the \nmind that uncovers evil and my sister is the arm that punishes it.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Seek out every supernatural creature and eliminate them in the name of God.\nGift - The Mind: White Rose is immune to any kind of \nmind control or fear effect, even if it is magical in origin. \nThrough her words, White Rose can interrupt mind control \nand fear effects on other targets. These effects end automatically on White Rose, while for other targets a Hunter is \nforced to make a Defense Check to keep their power active. \nRed Rose\nDescriptor: I hunt monsters and have trained my body \nsolely to fight the darkness. I am the arm that punishes evil \nand my sister is the mind that uncovers it.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Seek out every supernatural creature and eliminate them in the name of God.\nGift - The Arm: Red Rose increases her OL by 1 when she \nattacks a Broken Tale with the specific purpose of killing \nthem.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 18","owner":"White Rose and Red Rose","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-white-rose-and-red-rose-18","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":18}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>White Rose and Red Rose\nInspired by Snow-White and Rose-Red (Opponents)\nOnce upon a time, there was a poor widow who had two \ngood and hardworking daughters. White Rose and Red Rose \nwere the girls’ names. Both had a strict religious upbringing, following their Mother’s unwavering faith. The two \nsisters often played in the woods near the house, but \ntheir Mother feared nothing, convinced that her prayers \nmade the whole family immune to any misfortune. \nOne day, a strange talking Bear appeared at their door \nand told them that he was a prince cursed by an evil \nwitch. The woman and her daughters made the \nBear comfortable by offering him shelter. They \nfed him and kept him warm, and when he \nfell asleep, they mercilessly slit his throat. A \ntalking animal was surely the work of the \ndevil and as such had to be eliminated. A \nshort time later, a well-dressed Dwarf appeared at the house. He was looking for the \nprince he served, who had been cursed \nby an evil witch who had turned him \ninto a Bear. As a reward for finding \nhis master, the Dwarf offered a \nbag full of magical treasures. The \nwoman and her two daughters \nmade the Dwarf comfortable \nin the house, and they set \nabout sewing the cloak \nthat had been torn\n18\nfrom him on his journey. While the Mother prepared needle and thread, White Rose held the Dwarf down and Red \nRose thrust the scissors into his eyes. Blind and frightened, \nthe Dwarf tried to flee, but White Rose finished him off with \na deft blow. The offering of magical treasures was surely the \nwork of the devil, and once again the two young girls had \ncarried out God’s word as their Mother had intended. As the \nyears passed, the two girls became women. When their Mother ascended to heaven, she left her beloved daughters with \none last task: to find the devil in the world and put an end to \nhim, just as divine will dictates.\nWhite Rose\nDescriptor: I hunt monsters and I have learned every bit \nof knowledge relevant to the fight against darkness. I am the \nmind that uncovers evil and my sister is the arm that punishes it.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Seek out every supernatural creature and eliminate them in the name of God.\nGift - The Mind: White Rose is immune to any kind of \nmind control or fear effect, even if it is magical in origin. \nThrough her words, White Rose can interrupt mind control \nand fear effects on other targets. These effects end automatically on White Rose, while for other targets a Hunter is \nforced to make a Defense Check to keep their power active. \nRed Rose\nDescriptor: I hunt monsters and have trained my body \nsolely to fight the darkness. I am the arm that punishes evil \nand my sister is the mind that uncovers it.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Seek out every supernatural creature and eliminate them in the name of God.\nGift - The Arm: Red Rose increases her OL by 1 when she \nattacks a Broken Tale with the specific purpose of killing \nthem.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Seek out every supernatural creature and eliminate them in the name of God.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"60IeTAOt9QiiOmaK","name":"Brunhilde the Fighter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"gwV3snChtjjBK8On","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a seasoned commander, and my swordsmanship rivals even the most skilled warriors. I can tell the \nquality of a fighter at a glance.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 13","positive":"I am a seasoned commander, and my swordsmanship rivals even the most skilled warriors. I can tell the \nquality of a fighter at a glance.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"91CIT4pQhNRzwCRM","name":"Gift - She Who Chooses the Fallen","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>If Brunhilde fights \na subject she believes to be a brave warrior, she is considered to have OL Hard 7 and inflicts 1 Additional Wound for \neach strike with her sword. Brunhilde has a strong military pride and hates to raise her weapons against the \ndefenseless. Against a target she considers defenseless, \nBrunhilde is considered to have OL Easy 3.\n13</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 13","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eSuQpRG0n2ORcBd5","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Brunhilde the Fighter\nInspired by the Valkyrie of Norse Mythology \n(Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a commander named Brunhilde who distinguished herself in the field for her tactical \nskills. Under her leadership, soldiers were safe and losses \nwere kept to a minimum. Brunhilde had an illustrious career, \nracking up victories and quickly becoming the king’s favor -\nite. But all this made the other army \ncommanders jealous, and they \nhatched a plan to end Brunhilde’s success. By falsifying \ninformation from the field \nand presenting it as a \nnormal offensive action, \na suicide mission into \nthe heart of enemy \nterritory was \norganized. Brunhilde confidently led a thousand soldiers \ninto battle, only to find herself in the midst of a massacre. As \nthe soldiers fell like flies, cursing their commander, Brunhilde \nwent mad with guilt and began telling her subordinates that \nwhat was happening was written in fate. They were not going \nto die. Instead, they had been chosen to ascend into heaven, \nwhere an even greater and more glorious battle was in progress. Brunhilde was the only one to survive this conflict, and \nas punishment, she was banished from the army in disgrace. \nBut the madness had now taken root in the poor woman’s \nmind, and she began to wander in search of brave soldiers to \nascend to heaven and replenish the ranks of the divine army.\nDescriptor: I am a seasoned commander, and my swordsmanship rivals even the most skilled warriors. I can tell the \nquality of a fighter at a glance.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Identify and kill all individuals who I believe can \nbecome soldiers for the armies of heaven. \nGift - She Who Chooses the Fallen: If Brunhilde fights \na subject she believes to be a brave warrior, she is considered to have OL Hard 7 and inflicts 1 Additional Wound for \neach strike with her sword. Brunhilde has a strong military pride and hates to raise her weapons against the \ndefenseless. Against a target she considers defenseless, \nBrunhilde is considered to have OL Easy 3.\n13</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 13","owner":"Brunhilde the Fighter","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-brunhilde-the-fighter-13","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":13}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Brunhilde the Fighter\nInspired by the Valkyrie of Norse Mythology \n(Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a commander named Brunhilde who distinguished herself in the field for her tactical \nskills. Under her leadership, soldiers were safe and losses \nwere kept to a minimum. Brunhilde had an illustrious career, \nracking up victories and quickly becoming the king’s favor -\nite. But all this made the other army \ncommanders jealous, and they \nhatched a plan to end Brunhilde’s success. By falsifying \ninformation from the field \nand presenting it as a \nnormal offensive action, \na suicide mission into \nthe heart of enemy \nterritory was \norganized. Brunhilde confidently led a thousand soldiers \ninto battle, only to find herself in the midst of a massacre. As \nthe soldiers fell like flies, cursing their commander, Brunhilde \nwent mad with guilt and began telling her subordinates that \nwhat was happening was written in fate. They were not going \nto die. Instead, they had been chosen to ascend into heaven, \nwhere an even greater and more glorious battle was in progress. Brunhilde was the only one to survive this conflict, and \nas punishment, she was banished from the army in disgrace. \nBut the madness had now taken root in the poor woman’s \nmind, and she began to wander in search of brave soldiers to \nascend to heaven and replenish the ranks of the divine army.\nDescriptor: I am a seasoned commander, and my swordsmanship rivals even the most skilled warriors. I can tell the \nquality of a fighter at a glance.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Identify and kill all individuals who I believe can \nbecome soldiers for the armies of heaven. \nGift - She Who Chooses the Fallen: If Brunhilde fights \na subject she believes to be a brave warrior, she is considered to have OL Hard 7 and inflicts 1 Additional Wound for \neach strike with her sword. Brunhilde has a strong military pride and hates to raise her weapons against the \ndefenseless. Against a target she considers defenseless, \nBrunhilde is considered to have OL Easy 3.\n13</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Identify and kill all individuals who I believe can \nbecome soldiers for the armies of heaven.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AHtjegTXfWDl0UHG","name":"The Roc","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"R6pljRHeoewS7Sxn","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge egg, growing unnaturally large when \nsafely underground. My shell is hard as metal.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 14","positive":"I am a huge egg, growing unnaturally large when \nsafely underground. My shell is hard as metal.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zLJGRVsg8zKiJO1X","name":"Gift - Hatching","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The egg of the Roc grows when buried in \nsoil and will hatch within a year. Each month, the egg gains 1 \nHatching Token. When it reaches 12 Tokens, it will hatch and \ngive birth to the Roc. Magic nourishes the egg, so when a very \npowerful spell is cast near the nest, 1 Hatching Token is added \nas a side effect. Whenever 1 Hatching Token is added, the vibrations from the incubation will cause a natural disaster, such \nas an earthquake, which will cause extensive damage to the surrounding area.\nRoc</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 14","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OM4Sq2QmcE6grASO","name":"Gift - Wingflap","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>By flapping its giant wings, the Roc creates \ngusts of wind that can topple the houses of a city. Those hit by \nthe wind take 2 Penalties to any action.\n14</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 14","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"knnVMGAItv9YunK5","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Roc\nInspired by the Travels of Sinbad the Sailor \n(Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a greedy Merchant who traveled all \nthe way to the Ottoman Empire in search of rare and valuable \ngoods. In the distant lands of the south, the Merchant saw strange \ngiant eggs and asked where they came from. The sellers replied \nthat they were the very rare eggs of the Roc, a titanic bird that \ncame from the farthest deserts. The Merchant immediately asked \nthe price of this miracle but received a categorical refusal. It was \ntoo dangerous to give the eggs to a foreigner. But the Merchant \nwould not listen to reason and offered so much gold that the pile \ncovered the sellers up to their heads. Imagining the fortune he \nwould make at the courts and aristocratic drawing rooms, the \nMerchant set sail for Europe again, but two misguided Servants \nhad overheard the negotiations and plotted to get their hands \non the treasure. On the last night of the voyage, the two Ser -\nvants killed the Merchant and escaped in a lifeboat. Ironically, \nthe two scoundrels were caught in a rough sea that capsized \nthe boat, and as the Servants drowned, the five Roc eggs were \nlost to the current. Nearly a year later, a powerful earthquake shook the people of Cordova to the core. The earth \nsplit open, and from its bowels a giant creature took \nflight to return to its home, leaving only death \nand destruction in its wake.\nRoc’s Egg\nDescriptor: I am a huge egg, growing unnaturally large when \nsafely underground. My shell is hard as metal.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Grow by leaps and bounds to hatch.\nGift - Hatching: The egg of the Roc grows when buried in \nsoil and will hatch within a year. Each month, the egg gains 1 \nHatching Token. When it reaches 12 Tokens, it will hatch and \ngive birth to the Roc. Magic nourishes the egg, so when a very \npowerful spell is cast near the nest, 1 Hatching Token is added \nas a side effect. Whenever 1 Hatching Token is added, the vibrations from the incubation will cause a natural disaster, such \nas an earthquake, which will cause extensive damage to the surrounding area.\nRoc\nDescriptor: I am a huge bird with a wingspan of over sixty feet. \nWith a flap of my wings, I can create a whirlwind. \n5 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To return to the lands from which I came, regardless of \nthe damage caused by my leaving. \nGift - Wingflap: By flapping its giant wings, the Roc creates \ngusts of wind that can topple the houses of a city. Those hit by \nthe wind take 2 Penalties to any action.\n14</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 14","owner":"The Roc","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-the-roc-14","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":14}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Roc\nInspired by the Travels of Sinbad the Sailor \n(Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a greedy Merchant who traveled all \nthe way to the Ottoman Empire in search of rare and valuable \ngoods. In the distant lands of the south, the Merchant saw strange \ngiant eggs and asked where they came from. The sellers replied \nthat they were the very rare eggs of the Roc, a titanic bird that \ncame from the farthest deserts. The Merchant immediately asked \nthe price of this miracle but received a categorical refusal. It was \ntoo dangerous to give the eggs to a foreigner. But the Merchant \nwould not listen to reason and offered so much gold that the pile \ncovered the sellers up to their heads. Imagining the fortune he \nwould make at the courts and aristocratic drawing rooms, the \nMerchant set sail for Europe again, but two misguided Servants \nhad overheard the negotiations and plotted to get their hands \non the treasure. On the last night of the voyage, the two Ser -\nvants killed the Merchant and escaped in a lifeboat. Ironically, \nthe two scoundrels were caught in a rough sea that capsized \nthe boat, and as the Servants drowned, the five Roc eggs were \nlost to the current. Nearly a year later, a powerful earthquake shook the people of Cordova to the core. The earth \nsplit open, and from its bowels a giant creature took \nflight to return to its home, leaving only death \nand destruction in its wake.\nRoc’s Egg\nDescriptor: I am a huge egg, growing unnaturally large when \nsafely underground. My shell is hard as metal.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Hard 7\nAgenda: Grow by leaps and bounds to hatch.\nGift - Hatching: The egg of the Roc grows when buried in \nsoil and will hatch within a year. Each month, the egg gains 1 \nHatching Token. When it reaches 12 Tokens, it will hatch and \ngive birth to the Roc. Magic nourishes the egg, so when a very \npowerful spell is cast near the nest, 1 Hatching Token is added \nas a side effect. Whenever 1 Hatching Token is added, the vibrations from the incubation will cause a natural disaster, such \nas an earthquake, which will cause extensive damage to the surrounding area.\nRoc\nDescriptor: I am a huge bird with a wingspan of over sixty feet. \nWith a flap of my wings, I can create a whirlwind. \n5 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: To return to the lands from which I came, regardless of \nthe damage caused by my leaving. \nGift - Wingflap: By flapping its giant wings, the Roc creates \ngusts of wind that can topple the houses of a city. Those hit by \nthe wind take 2 Penalties to any action.\n14</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Grow by leaps and bounds to hatch.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"K4Gpr0v7e0H4r4hx","name":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"98DxBBf9SqgR42TH","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled doctor who can operate with extreme precision. \nWith my scalpels, I can extract a tooth with a single stroke.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 7","positive":"I am a skilled doctor who can operate with extreme precision. \nWith my scalpels, I can extract a tooth with a single stroke.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NYeLC5n2ZDQRywMJ","name":"Gift - Surgical Precision","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Polonia’s scalpel skills are so precise that \nshe can extract a tooth in a single stroke. Once per Scene, Polonia can use \nan action to inflict 1 Additional Wound by attacking with her scalpel. If \nher victim is asleep, Polonia can operate for as long as she wishes without \nwaking them.\nPerez “the Rat”</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 7","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V8oGiYZhx8RToRl8","name":"Gift - Brawler","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Against Perez, Gifts that grant bonuses in \ncombat have no effect.\n8</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 7","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Vr1K2YLbYITKQstT","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>.Polonia “the \nFairy” and Perez \n“the Rat” \nInspired by the Tooth Fairy and the Little Mouse \n(Neutral)\nSelling components to witches and sorcerers for their rituals is highly profitable, and many mercenaries throw themselves into this field to amass great wealth. One of the most \nfamous couples in this field is that of Polonia, known as the \nFairy, a doctor specializing in dentistry, and Perez, known \nas The Rat, a sinewy grave robber. The two apparently met \nwhile plundering the crypt of a wealthy nobleman on behalf \nof a mysterious sorcerer. Passion was ignited amidst family \ntreasures and corpses, and from that day forward, Polonia \nand Perez became partners in both work and love. The two \ndiscovered that their mysterious patron wanted the teeth of \nthe wealthy dead since teeth are perfect catalysts of power for \ncertain magical practices. Aware that they had an untapped \nmarket on their hands, Polonia and Perez became tooth dealers, amassing horrendous quantities of them and becoming \nthe main point of contact for all European magicians. The \nconstant demand for this type of merchandise soon exhausted the teeth of the dead, however, and Polonia and Perez willingly switched to the living.\n7\nPolonia “the Fairy”\nDescriptor: I am a skilled doctor who can operate with extreme precision. \nWith my scalpels, I can extract a tooth with a single stroke.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Procuring teeth for my trade without caring who the victim is. I \nhate being conspicuous, so I prefer to operate on sleeping patients.\nGift - Surgical Precision: Polonia’s scalpel skills are so precise that \nshe can extract a tooth in a single stroke. Once per Scene, Polonia can use \nan action to inflict 1 Additional Wound by attacking with her scalpel. If \nher victim is asleep, Polonia can operate for as long as she wishes without \nwaking them.\nPerez “the Rat”\nDescriptor: Where my partner works with precision, I am more \ndirect. With one punch I can shatter any smile. My physique is \npowerful and I am used to bare-knuckle fighting.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: I procure teeth for my business without caring who \nthe victim is. I always leave the valuable merchandise to Polania’s skilled hands, while I make up the numbers by knocking out \nlow-value teeth with my fists.\nGift - Brawler: Against Perez, Gifts that grant bonuses in \ncombat have no effect.\n8</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 7","owner":"Polonia “the Fairy” and Perez “the Rat”","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-polonia-the-fairy-and-perez-the-rat-7","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":7}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>.Polonia “the \nFairy” and Perez \n“the Rat” \nInspired by the Tooth Fairy and the Little Mouse \n(Neutral)\nSelling components to witches and sorcerers for their rituals is highly profitable, and many mercenaries throw themselves into this field to amass great wealth. One of the most \nfamous couples in this field is that of Polonia, known as the \nFairy, a doctor specializing in dentistry, and Perez, known \nas The Rat, a sinewy grave robber. The two apparently met \nwhile plundering the crypt of a wealthy nobleman on behalf \nof a mysterious sorcerer. Passion was ignited amidst family \ntreasures and corpses, and from that day forward, Polonia \nand Perez became partners in both work and love. The two \ndiscovered that their mysterious patron wanted the teeth of \nthe wealthy dead since teeth are perfect catalysts of power for \ncertain magical practices. Aware that they had an untapped \nmarket on their hands, Polonia and Perez became tooth dealers, amassing horrendous quantities of them and becoming \nthe main point of contact for all European magicians. The \nconstant demand for this type of merchandise soon exhausted the teeth of the dead, however, and Polonia and Perez willingly switched to the living.\n7\nPolonia “the Fairy”\nDescriptor: I am a skilled doctor who can operate with extreme precision. \nWith my scalpels, I can extract a tooth with a single stroke.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Procuring teeth for my trade without caring who the victim is. I \nhate being conspicuous, so I prefer to operate on sleeping patients.\nGift - Surgical Precision: Polonia’s scalpel skills are so precise that \nshe can extract a tooth in a single stroke. Once per Scene, Polonia can use \nan action to inflict 1 Additional Wound by attacking with her scalpel. If \nher victim is asleep, Polonia can operate for as long as she wishes without \nwaking them.\nPerez “the Rat”\nDescriptor: Where my partner works with precision, I am more \ndirect. With one punch I can shatter any smile. My physique is \npowerful and I am used to bare-knuckle fighting.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: I procure teeth for my business without caring who \nthe victim is. I always leave the valuable merchandise to Polania’s skilled hands, while I make up the numbers by knocking out \nlow-value teeth with my fists.\nGift - Brawler: Against Perez, Gifts that grant bonuses in \ncombat have no effect.\n8</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Procuring teeth for my trade without caring who the victim is. I \nhate being conspicuous, so I prefer to operate on sleeping patients.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Mq4A5gddw3wKXTDk","name":"Hans the Handsome","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"HDBs8292hNdIAdFr","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am adept at flushing out and dealing with \nbeasts of all kinds. I avoid any reflective surface, for I cannot \nbear the sight of my true self.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 11","positive":"I am adept at flushing out and dealing with \nbeasts of all kinds. I avoid any reflective surface, for I cannot \nbear the sight of my true self.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"E2pAgXoiyhgimUYr","name":"Gift - Handsome on the Outside","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hans has a hand -\nsome appearance and charm that cannot be ignored. \nIn all situations where his physical appearance can be \nused to his advantage, he is considered OL Hard 7.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 11","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tpSxMOH4mfZa7Cdt","name":"Gift - Ugly on the Inside","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hans hates the beauty of \nothers with all his heart. When he wounds someone \nhe considers beautiful, the injuries are intended to \ndisfigure the target, which must create an appropriate Descriptor. Wounds inflicted in this way cannot \nbe healed by the use of Gifts, but only during an \nInterlude.\n12</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 11","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"b9rNWwntxh5O60FV","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hans the Handsome\nInspired by the Ugly Duckling (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was an ugly and clumsy little Duckling who, rejected and ridiculed by his peers, decided to run \naway in search of a different life. Caught in a snowstorm, the \nDuckling was in danger of freezing to death, but was rescued by an old Huntsman who took him into the warmth of \nhis shelter. After being warmed up, the Duckling asked the \nHuntsman how he could repay him, and the man asked him \nto help him on his next hunting trip. With the cold of winter, \nit was hard to find game, and the Duckling was good bait. \n“But I’m ugly, no one would come near me, ” said the Duckling. \n“ All they have to do is hear your call, ” replied the Huntsman, \n“and before they see you, I will have killed them. ” The next \nday they went hunting, and thanks to the little Duckling’s call, \nthe old Huntsman killed nine ducks. Satisfied, the Huntsman \nasked the little Duckling to continue their partnership. The \nlittle Duckling thought about it and finally agreed. It was a \ngood way to make those who had always rejected him pay \ndearly. Years passed, and the Huntsman, on his deathbed, \nsummoned a powerful Witch and bought from her a wish for \nhis hunting companion.\n“What is your wish?” the Witch asked the Duckling, and he \nreplied, “Turn me into a man. I want to be beautiful, so beautiful that everyone will have to stop and admire me. ” The \nWitch nodded and cast her spell. Once human, Hans (that \nwas the name the Duckling chose for himself) touched his \nface with his hands: his features were delicate, his hair light, \nlong, and flowing. He ran to the mirror, but what he saw in \nthe reflection was a frightening figure: eyes crooked and hol11\nlow, hair black and dirty, skin as scaly as a snake’s.\n“You promised me a beautiful body!” cried Hans. “ And that is \nwhat I have given you, ” replied the Witch. “Everyone else will \nsee you as dashing and handsome, but what only you will see \nin the mirror is your soul. ”\nDescriptor: I am adept at flushing out and dealing with \nbeasts of all kinds. I avoid any reflective surface, for I cannot \nbear the sight of my true self.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Stalking my prey / Being adored for my loveliness \n/ Breaking every mirror in my vicinity.\nGift - Handsome on the Outside: Hans has a hand -\nsome appearance and charm that cannot be ignored. \nIn all situations where his physical appearance can be \nused to his advantage, he is considered OL Hard 7.\nGift - Ugly on the Inside: Hans hates the beauty of \nothers with all his heart. When he wounds someone \nhe considers beautiful, the injuries are intended to \ndisfigure the target, which must create an appropriate Descriptor. Wounds inflicted in this way cannot \nbe healed by the use of Gifts, but only during an \nInterlude.\n12</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 11","owner":"Hans the Handsome","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-hans-the-handsome-11","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":11}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Hans the Handsome\nInspired by the Ugly Duckling (Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was an ugly and clumsy little Duckling who, rejected and ridiculed by his peers, decided to run \naway in search of a different life. Caught in a snowstorm, the \nDuckling was in danger of freezing to death, but was rescued by an old Huntsman who took him into the warmth of \nhis shelter. After being warmed up, the Duckling asked the \nHuntsman how he could repay him, and the man asked him \nto help him on his next hunting trip. With the cold of winter, \nit was hard to find game, and the Duckling was good bait. \n“But I’m ugly, no one would come near me, ” said the Duckling. \n“ All they have to do is hear your call, ” replied the Huntsman, \n“and before they see you, I will have killed them. ” The next \nday they went hunting, and thanks to the little Duckling’s call, \nthe old Huntsman killed nine ducks. Satisfied, the Huntsman \nasked the little Duckling to continue their partnership. The \nlittle Duckling thought about it and finally agreed. It was a \ngood way to make those who had always rejected him pay \ndearly. Years passed, and the Huntsman, on his deathbed, \nsummoned a powerful Witch and bought from her a wish for \nhis hunting companion.\n“What is your wish?” the Witch asked the Duckling, and he \nreplied, “Turn me into a man. I want to be beautiful, so beautiful that everyone will have to stop and admire me. ” The \nWitch nodded and cast her spell. Once human, Hans (that \nwas the name the Duckling chose for himself) touched his \nface with his hands: his features were delicate, his hair light, \nlong, and flowing. He ran to the mirror, but what he saw in \nthe reflection was a frightening figure: eyes crooked and hol11\nlow, hair black and dirty, skin as scaly as a snake’s.\n“You promised me a beautiful body!” cried Hans. “ And that is \nwhat I have given you, ” replied the Witch. “Everyone else will \nsee you as dashing and handsome, but what only you will see \nin the mirror is your soul. ”\nDescriptor: I am adept at flushing out and dealing with \nbeasts of all kinds. I avoid any reflective surface, for I cannot \nbear the sight of my true self.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Stalking my prey / Being adored for my loveliness \n/ Breaking every mirror in my vicinity.\nGift - Handsome on the Outside: Hans has a hand -\nsome appearance and charm that cannot be ignored. \nIn all situations where his physical appearance can be \nused to his advantage, he is considered OL Hard 7.\nGift - Ugly on the Inside: Hans hates the beauty of \nothers with all his heart. When he wounds someone \nhe considers beautiful, the injuries are intended to \ndisfigure the target, which must create an appropriate Descriptor. Wounds inflicted in this way cannot \nbe healed by the use of Gifts, but only during an \nInterlude.\n12</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Stalking my prey / Being adored for my loveliness \n/ Breaking every mirror in my vicinity.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RREoyllpefT5LLrP","name":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"LMozGMUfDUlAwCAe","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor boy who no longer has a home \nto live in. I dabble in painting and can turn my hand to all \nkinds of work.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 15","positive":"I am a poor boy who no longer has a home \nto live in. I dabble in painting and can turn my hand to all \nkinds of work.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"e5ryAbOzmxEUGuIf","name":"Gift - Poor and Unlucky","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Nello has bad luck and is \nalways in the wrong place at the wrong time. He may ap15\npear during a Scene in which an illegal act is taking place \nor a secret is being revealed that no one should know. Nello \nwill appear by chance, completely unaware of the danger he \nis in. When introduced into the game, Nello will always have \na connection to an evil NPC who is using the young man for \npersonal gain.\nThe Faithful Patrasche</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 15","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iL0OD4VVTiWldKEj","name":"Gift - Monstrous","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Although he appears as a simple dog, \nPatrasche can take his true form, becoming a huge and monstrously ravenous wolf. In this form, Patrasche increases his \nOL by 1 when he acts to defend Nello. When Patrasche is revealed for what he really is, ordinary people flee in terror, Minor NPCs will never choose to attack him, and Main NPCs \ndecrease their OL by 1. A Hunter must pass a Defense Check \nto avoid being shaken by the sight and receive 1 Penalty on \nany action while Patrasche is in the Scene.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 15","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KMF1sj8klypWWD1A","name":"Gift - Loyal Friend","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, if Nello is in danger, \nPatrasche can appear out of nowhere in his monstrous wolf \nform to defend his little friend.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 15","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IxmVD6Blfk5gvVdD","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Poor Nello and The \nFaithful Patrasche\nInspired by A Dog of Flanders (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a poor boy named Nello, for \nwhom fate had reserved only suffering. Orphaned at a young \nage, Nello lived with his elderly grandfather and earned \na few coins by selling milk on the streets of Antwerp. One \nday, word spread that a terrible creature was stalking its \nprey near the city. Immediately, groups of soldiers set out to \nhunt down the monster. When they returned, the captain \nof the guard swore that the terrible beast had been mortally \nwounded. That same evening, on his way home, Nello found \na huge wounded dog along the road. Without giving it much \nthought, Nello dragged the animal home and took care of it. \nMonths passed and the dog made a full recovery, becoming \nvery loyal to his new master. Nello named him Patrasche, \nand the two became inseparable. But that was the only joy \nin a life of hardship for the little boy. One evening, a group of \ncutthroats appeared at the door of Nello’s home and threatened his little family. Nello’s grandfather had borrowed \nmoney to get by, and now his tormentors were demanding \nit back with stratospheric interest. The ruffians attacked the \npoor grandfather. Nello tried to defend him, but a blow to \nthe head knocked him unconscious. When he regained consciousness, he found himself surrounded by the remains of a \nbloodbath, the dismembered bodies of the cutthroats and his \npoor grandfather scattered everywhere. In the middle, the \nfaithful Patrasche wagged his tail, happy to have saved his \nmaster.\nPoor Nello\nDescriptor: I am a poor boy who no longer has a home \nto live in. I dabble in painting and can turn my hand to all \nkinds of work. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: To fulfill my dream of becoming a painter. \nGift - Poor and Unlucky: Nello has bad luck and is \nalways in the wrong place at the wrong time. He may ap15\npear during a Scene in which an illegal act is taking place \nor a secret is being revealed that no one should know. Nello \nwill appear by chance, completely unaware of the danger he \nis in. When introduced into the game, Nello will always have \na connection to an evil NPC who is using the young man for \npersonal gain.\nThe Faithful Patrasche\nDescriptor: I am a great monster, and my ferocity is matched \nonly by my strength. I take the form of a simple dog to deceive \nhumans and stay close to Nello, the only one I consider a friend.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Protect Nello by tearing apart any danger that \nthreatens him / Feed on people to satisfy my hunger without \nNello discovering my true nature.\nGift - Monstrous: Although he appears as a simple dog, \nPatrasche can take his true form, becoming a huge and monstrously ravenous wolf. In this form, Patrasche increases his \nOL by 1 when he acts to defend Nello. When Patrasche is revealed for what he really is, ordinary people flee in terror, Minor NPCs will never choose to attack him, and Main NPCs \ndecrease their OL by 1. A Hunter must pass a Defense Check \nto avoid being shaken by the sight and receive 1 Penalty on \nany action while Patrasche is in the Scene.\nGift - Loyal Friend: Once per Scene, if Nello is in danger, \nPatrasche can appear out of nowhere in his monstrous wolf \nform to defend his little friend.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 15","owner":"Poor Nello and The Faithful Patrasche","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-poor-nello-and-the-faithful-patrasche-15","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":15}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Poor Nello and The \nFaithful Patrasche\nInspired by A Dog of Flanders (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a poor boy named Nello, for \nwhom fate had reserved only suffering. Orphaned at a young \nage, Nello lived with his elderly grandfather and earned \na few coins by selling milk on the streets of Antwerp. One \nday, word spread that a terrible creature was stalking its \nprey near the city. Immediately, groups of soldiers set out to \nhunt down the monster. When they returned, the captain \nof the guard swore that the terrible beast had been mortally \nwounded. That same evening, on his way home, Nello found \na huge wounded dog along the road. Without giving it much \nthought, Nello dragged the animal home and took care of it. \nMonths passed and the dog made a full recovery, becoming \nvery loyal to his new master. Nello named him Patrasche, \nand the two became inseparable. But that was the only joy \nin a life of hardship for the little boy. One evening, a group of \ncutthroats appeared at the door of Nello’s home and threatened his little family. Nello’s grandfather had borrowed \nmoney to get by, and now his tormentors were demanding \nit back with stratospheric interest. The ruffians attacked the \npoor grandfather. Nello tried to defend him, but a blow to \nthe head knocked him unconscious. When he regained consciousness, he found himself surrounded by the remains of a \nbloodbath, the dismembered bodies of the cutthroats and his \npoor grandfather scattered everywhere. In the middle, the \nfaithful Patrasche wagged his tail, happy to have saved his \nmaster.\nPoor Nello\nDescriptor: I am a poor boy who no longer has a home \nto live in. I dabble in painting and can turn my hand to all \nkinds of work. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: To fulfill my dream of becoming a painter. \nGift - Poor and Unlucky: Nello has bad luck and is \nalways in the wrong place at the wrong time. He may ap15\npear during a Scene in which an illegal act is taking place \nor a secret is being revealed that no one should know. Nello \nwill appear by chance, completely unaware of the danger he \nis in. When introduced into the game, Nello will always have \na connection to an evil NPC who is using the young man for \npersonal gain.\nThe Faithful Patrasche\nDescriptor: I am a great monster, and my ferocity is matched \nonly by my strength. I take the form of a simple dog to deceive \nhumans and stay close to Nello, the only one I consider a friend.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Protect Nello by tearing apart any danger that \nthreatens him / Feed on people to satisfy my hunger without \nNello discovering my true nature.\nGift - Monstrous: Although he appears as a simple dog, \nPatrasche can take his true form, becoming a huge and monstrously ravenous wolf. In this form, Patrasche increases his \nOL by 1 when he acts to defend Nello. When Patrasche is revealed for what he really is, ordinary people flee in terror, Minor NPCs will never choose to attack him, and Main NPCs \ndecrease their OL by 1. A Hunter must pass a Defense Check \nto avoid being shaken by the sight and receive 1 Penalty on \nany action while Patrasche is in the Scene.\nGift - Loyal Friend: Once per Scene, if Nello is in danger, \nPatrasche can appear out of nowhere in his monstrous wolf \nform to defend his little friend.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To fulfill my dream of becoming a painter.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UUSnEcrlaKXhSBmf","name":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"bqVVUvtBMbKCXPGa","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a good-natured acrobat who enjoys music and poetry. \nThanks to my friendly nature, I can make everyone like me.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","positive":"I am a good-natured acrobat who enjoys music and poetry. \nThanks to my friendly nature, I can make everyone like me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VdcToLwBLIsr2pnl","name":"Gift - Yokai Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Gemba Tanuki can change his appearance \nat will so that he always looks like a different person. There are \nsome limitations to this power, however: he cannot take on the \nappearance of a specific subject, he cannot take on the form of \na female subject, and each identity shares a characteristically \nprominent belly.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HjzgRO8pDpL5K8E2","name":"Gift - The Possession Scam","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Gemba truly possesses \nsome exorcist powers and is therefore able to see Broken \nTales and Hunters for what they really are. A Hunter can \nmake a Defense Check to prevent Gemba from reading \ntheir true nature.\n10\nMayu Kitsune</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lb3rWxA5GwEadA6o","name":"Gift - Yokai Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Mayu Kitsune can change her appearance at will so that she always looks like a different \nperson. There are some limitations to this power, however: \nshe cannot take on the appearance of a specific subject, she \ncannot take on the form of a male subject, and each identity \npossesses a fox tail that Mayu must conceal somehow.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7CKQfEjpRWxOzxm3","name":"Gift - The Possession Scam","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Mayu can take control of \na Minor NPC by biting them and transferring herself into \ntheir body. As long as the possession is active, Mayu can \nact at will through the host’s body but does not gain their \nmemories or knowledge. Suffering a Wound or being the \ntarget of a hex-breaking spell will force Mayu to leave the \npossessed body.\nSpecial Agenda (Karasu Kuroi the Wandering \nMonk): That boring monk talks so much about justice and \nhonesty, but he conceals his true nature as much as we do. \nFor once, we will be the ones to expose a fraud.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Nwj9ZPU7LgBjj1YY","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune\nInspired by the Yokai of Japanese tradition (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a duo of skilled con artists who enjoyed robbing the wealthy families of Japan. \nGemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune were two Yokai who could change their appearance to suit their need, \nallowing them to fool many unsuspecting people. The duo’s most well-rehearsed scam was to use Mayu’s \npower of possession to take control of a high-ranking young female scion and fake an exorcism to free \nher through the prayers of Gemba, who pretended to be an exorcist monk. The duo became so \nfamous that they attracted the attention of the fearsome Yokai Hunters, the Japanese equivalent of the Hunters of the Order. Backed into a corner, the two scoundrels were forced \nto take to the sea and flee to Europe in search of new places to carry out their scams.\nGemba Tanuki\nDescriptor: I am a good-natured acrobat who enjoys music and poetry. \nThanks to my friendly nature, I can make everyone like me. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Make money through the well-trodden Possession Scam. \nGift - Yokai Spirit: Gemba Tanuki can change his appearance \nat will so that he always looks like a different person. There are \nsome limitations to this power, however: he cannot take on the \nappearance of a specific subject, he cannot take on the form of \na female subject, and each identity shares a characteristically \nprominent belly.\nGift - The Possession Scam: Gemba truly possesses \nsome exorcist powers and is therefore able to see Broken \nTales and Hunters for what they really are. A Hunter can \nmake a Defense Check to prevent Gemba from reading \ntheir true nature.\n10\nMayu Kitsune\nDescriptor: I am an attractive performer, skilled in dancing and singing. Thanks to my charm, I make many suitors \nfall at my feet. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Make money through the well-trodden Possession \nScam.\nGift - Yokai Spirit: Mayu Kitsune can change her appearance at will so that she always looks like a different \nperson. There are some limitations to this power, however: \nshe cannot take on the appearance of a specific subject, she \ncannot take on the form of a male subject, and each identity \npossesses a fox tail that Mayu must conceal somehow. \nGift - The Possession Scam: Mayu can take control of \na Minor NPC by biting them and transferring herself into \ntheir body. As long as the possession is active, Mayu can \nact at will through the host’s body but does not gain their \nmemories or knowledge. Suffering a Wound or being the \ntarget of a hex-breaking spell will force Mayu to leave the \npossessed body.\nSpecial Agenda (Karasu Kuroi the Wandering \nMonk): That boring monk talks so much about justice and \nhonesty, but he conceals his true nature as much as we do. \nFor once, we will be the ones to expose a fraud.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 10","owner":"Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-gemba-tanuki-and-mayu-kitsune-10","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":10}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Gemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune\nInspired by the Yokai of Japanese tradition (Neutral)\nOnce upon a time, there was a duo of skilled con artists who enjoyed robbing the wealthy families of Japan. \nGemba Tanuki and Mayu Kitsune were two Yokai who could change their appearance to suit their need, \nallowing them to fool many unsuspecting people. The duo’s most well-rehearsed scam was to use Mayu’s \npower of possession to take control of a high-ranking young female scion and fake an exorcism to free \nher through the prayers of Gemba, who pretended to be an exorcist monk. The duo became so \nfamous that they attracted the attention of the fearsome Yokai Hunters, the Japanese equivalent of the Hunters of the Order. Backed into a corner, the two scoundrels were forced \nto take to the sea and flee to Europe in search of new places to carry out their scams.\nGemba Tanuki\nDescriptor: I am a good-natured acrobat who enjoys music and poetry. \nThanks to my friendly nature, I can make everyone like me. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Make money through the well-trodden Possession Scam. \nGift - Yokai Spirit: Gemba Tanuki can change his appearance \nat will so that he always looks like a different person. There are \nsome limitations to this power, however: he cannot take on the \nappearance of a specific subject, he cannot take on the form of \na female subject, and each identity shares a characteristically \nprominent belly.\nGift - The Possession Scam: Gemba truly possesses \nsome exorcist powers and is therefore able to see Broken \nTales and Hunters for what they really are. A Hunter can \nmake a Defense Check to prevent Gemba from reading \ntheir true nature.\n10\nMayu Kitsune\nDescriptor: I am an attractive performer, skilled in dancing and singing. Thanks to my charm, I make many suitors \nfall at my feet. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Make money through the well-trodden Possession \nScam.\nGift - Yokai Spirit: Mayu Kitsune can change her appearance at will so that she always looks like a different \nperson. There are some limitations to this power, however: \nshe cannot take on the appearance of a specific subject, she \ncannot take on the form of a male subject, and each identity \npossesses a fox tail that Mayu must conceal somehow. \nGift - The Possession Scam: Mayu can take control of \na Minor NPC by biting them and transferring herself into \ntheir body. As long as the possession is active, Mayu can \nact at will through the host’s body but does not gain their \nmemories or knowledge. Suffering a Wound or being the \ntarget of a hex-breaking spell will force Mayu to leave the \npossessed body.\nSpecial Agenda (Karasu Kuroi the Wandering \nMonk): That boring monk talks so much about justice and \nhonesty, but he conceals his true nature as much as we do. \nFor once, we will be the ones to expose a fraud.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Make money through the well-trodden Possession Scam.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"axePrK6dbQGZIdgI","name":"The Regiment of Giants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"mKVBKTDWGPABGmal","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are cowards and poorly trained soldiers, \nbut our reputation as fearsome Giants allows us to fool people.\n1 Wound (20 Company members)</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 9","positive":"We are cowards and poorly trained soldiers, \nbut our reputation as fearsome Giants allows us to fool people.\n1 Wound (20 Company members)","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BTOkPKRWdjkdufQk","name":"Gift - Here Come the Giants","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>All normal humans fear \nthe Giants and have heard stories of their incredible ferocity. No NPC who is not a Broken Tale will act directly against \nthe Giants. Even the Hunters are afraid of the Giants, so \nany action against them will result in 1 Penalty. Once the \nGiants’ inability has been demonstrated, the effect of this \nGift no longer applies to anyone who witnesses the scene.\n9</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 9","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"L3DQjOMS7o2ZgMt6","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Regiment of \nGiants\nInspired by the Giants of many fairytales \n(Opponents)\nOnce upon a time, there was a King with very bizarre ideas, \none of which was creating a regiment of real Giants. The King \nwas a great lover of myths and stories, and he was convinced \nthat nothing could frighten his enemies more than an imposing Giant. So the first Regiment of Giants was formed in the \ncity of Potsdam, including about 20 giants from all over Europe. The Giants inspired awe with their mere presence, but \nduring a particularly peaceful period, they never once had to \nprove themselves on the battlefield. Worshiped and cared for \nwithout having to do more than march in public parades, the \nGiants soon became lazy and forgot all training. When the \nextravagant King was deposed by his son, the Regiment of \nGiants was immediately disbanded, and its members found \nthemselves on their own for the first time. Devoid of skill, \nbut still feared and famous, the Giants formed \ntheir own mercenary company in the hopes \nof scraping together some spare change \nby trading on their fame, while hoping \nthey would never have to prove \nanything in the field.\nDescriptor: We are cowards and poorly trained soldiers, \nbut our reputation as fearsome Giants allows us to fool people.\n1 Wound (20 Company members)\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Serving those who hired us and using the fear we \ninstill as a weapon to solve any problem / Avoiding actual \naction as much as possible. \nGift - Here Come the Giants: All normal humans fear \nthe Giants and have heard stories of their incredible ferocity. No NPC who is not a Broken Tale will act directly against \nthe Giants. Even the Hunters are afraid of the Giants, so \nany action against them will result in 1 Penalty. Once the \nGiants’ inability has been demonstrated, the effect of this \nGift no longer applies to anyone who witnesses the scene.\n9</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 9","owner":"The Regiment of Giants","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-the-regiment-of-giants-9","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":9}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Regiment of \nGiants\nInspired by the Giants of many fairytales \n(Opponents)\nOnce upon a time, there was a King with very bizarre ideas, \none of which was creating a regiment of real Giants. The King \nwas a great lover of myths and stories, and he was convinced \nthat nothing could frighten his enemies more than an imposing Giant. So the first Regiment of Giants was formed in the \ncity of Potsdam, including about 20 giants from all over Europe. The Giants inspired awe with their mere presence, but \nduring a particularly peaceful period, they never once had to \nprove themselves on the battlefield. Worshiped and cared for \nwithout having to do more than march in public parades, the \nGiants soon became lazy and forgot all training. When the \nextravagant King was deposed by his son, the Regiment of \nGiants was immediately disbanded, and its members found \nthemselves on their own for the first time. Devoid of skill, \nbut still feared and famous, the Giants formed \ntheir own mercenary company in the hopes \nof scraping together some spare change \nby trading on their fame, while hoping \nthey would never have to prove \nanything in the field.\nDescriptor: We are cowards and poorly trained soldiers, \nbut our reputation as fearsome Giants allows us to fool people.\n1 Wound (20 Company members)\nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Serving those who hired us and using the fear we \ninstill as a weapon to solve any problem / Avoiding actual \naction as much as possible. \nGift - Here Come the Giants: All normal humans fear \nthe Giants and have heard stories of their incredible ferocity. No NPC who is not a Broken Tale will act directly against \nthe Giants. Even the Hunters are afraid of the Giants, so \nany action against them will result in 1 Penalty. Once the \nGiants’ inability has been demonstrated, the effect of this \nGift no longer applies to anyone who witnesses the scene.\n9</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Serving those who hired us and using the fear we \ninstill as a weapon to solve any problem / Avoiding actual \naction as much as possible.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dapVuEn0roYEocUn","name":"Harlequin the Servant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"2QKY2anuJ4WKEnmH","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled servant and can adapt to any task given to me. I \nalways find ways to carry out orders with as little effort as possible.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 6","positive":"I am a skilled servant and can adapt to any task given to me. I \nalways find ways to carry out orders with as little effort as possible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"siyUB6grdJATAkrG","name":"Gift - Skillful and Unwilling","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Harlequin can do anything he is orde -\nred to. During a Scene, a Hunter can make a request to Harlequin, \nsuch as “Find out this person’s secrets” or “Deliver this letter with6\nout being seen. ” Harlequin will appear at the beginning of the \nnext Scene, having completed the task. He will categorically \nrefuse to hurt anyone or, more generally, to use violence. \nAs skilled as he is, Harlequin is also incredibly unwilling \nto serve. At the beginning of the Scenario, the Storyteller \nsecretly rolls a die to determine which vice he indulges in.\n1-2 Slacker: Harlequin has very little desire to work, and \nwhen he does perform a task, he does so by following exactly what he has been told. For example, if the request is \n“Deliver this letter without being seen, ” he will not even be \nseen by the recipient of the letter, without caring if they \nread it or not.\n3-4 Servant of Two Masters: Harlequin divides his \nservices between the Hunters and one of the Scenario’s \nMain NPCs. When he completes a job for the Hunters, the \nMain NPC will be notified.\n5-6 In Love: Harlequin is in love with a beautiful young \nwoman and takes advantage of every moment to be with \nher. When he leaves the Scene to perform a task, the Storyteller rolls a second die: if the result is even, Harlequin \nreturns as usual at the beginning of the next Scene. If the \nresult is odd, Harlequin returns in the middle of a Scene \nthat has already begun, making up an imaginative excuse \nto justify his delay.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 6","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"508VDQDFP0fqf2Y8","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Harlequin the Servant\nInspired by Harlequin of the Italian tradition (Ally)\nMany are under the Order’s “special” surveillance, men and women with gifts above \nthe norm but not enough to make them candidates for full-fledged Hunters. For \nmany of them, the role of aide is enough, and many are happy to join the ranks of \nthe Order in this way. Many, but not Harlequin. This strange figure, who likes to \nwear garish robes, has long been a servant of the Order, a role he fills with ill-concealed reluctance and great skill. No one knows his real name or origin, and some \nrumors within the Order say he is the Devil himself, who likes to disguise himself \nto mock the Church. All that is certain is that Harlequin is the most capable of \nservants, but only when he feels like doing his duty...\nDescriptor: I am a skilled servant and can adapt to any task given to me. I \nalways find ways to carry out orders with as little effort as possible.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Helping the Hunters as ordered by the Church, but never letting \ngo of having fun. \nGift - Skillful and Unwilling: Harlequin can do anything he is orde -\nred to. During a Scene, a Hunter can make a request to Harlequin, \nsuch as “Find out this person’s secrets” or “Deliver this letter with6\nout being seen. ” Harlequin will appear at the beginning of the \nnext Scene, having completed the task. He will categorically \nrefuse to hurt anyone or, more generally, to use violence. \nAs skilled as he is, Harlequin is also incredibly unwilling \nto serve. At the beginning of the Scenario, the Storyteller \nsecretly rolls a die to determine which vice he indulges in.\n1-2 Slacker: Harlequin has very little desire to work, and \nwhen he does perform a task, he does so by following exactly what he has been told. For example, if the request is \n“Deliver this letter without being seen, ” he will not even be \nseen by the recipient of the letter, without caring if they \nread it or not.\n3-4 Servant of Two Masters: Harlequin divides his \nservices between the Hunters and one of the Scenario’s \nMain NPCs. When he completes a job for the Hunters, the \nMain NPC will be notified.\n5-6 In Love: Harlequin is in love with a beautiful young \nwoman and takes advantage of every moment to be with \nher. When he leaves the Scene to perform a task, the Storyteller rolls a second die: if the result is even, Harlequin \nreturns as usual at the beginning of the next Scene. If the \nresult is odd, Harlequin returns in the middle of a Scene \nthat has already begun, making up an imaginative excuse \nto justify his delay.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 6","owner":"Harlequin the Servant","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-harlequin-the-servant-6","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":6}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>Harlequin the Servant\nInspired by Harlequin of the Italian tradition (Ally)\nMany are under the Order’s “special” surveillance, men and women with gifts above \nthe norm but not enough to make them candidates for full-fledged Hunters. For \nmany of them, the role of aide is enough, and many are happy to join the ranks of \nthe Order in this way. Many, but not Harlequin. This strange figure, who likes to \nwear garish robes, has long been a servant of the Order, a role he fills with ill-concealed reluctance and great skill. No one knows his real name or origin, and some \nrumors within the Order say he is the Devil himself, who likes to disguise himself \nto mock the Church. All that is certain is that Harlequin is the most capable of \nservants, but only when he feels like doing his duty...\nDescriptor: I am a skilled servant and can adapt to any task given to me. I \nalways find ways to carry out orders with as little effort as possible.\n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Medium 5\nAgenda: Helping the Hunters as ordered by the Church, but never letting \ngo of having fun. \nGift - Skillful and Unwilling: Harlequin can do anything he is orde -\nred to. During a Scene, a Hunter can make a request to Harlequin, \nsuch as “Find out this person’s secrets” or “Deliver this letter with6\nout being seen. ” Harlequin will appear at the beginning of the \nnext Scene, having completed the task. He will categorically \nrefuse to hurt anyone or, more generally, to use violence. \nAs skilled as he is, Harlequin is also incredibly unwilling \nto serve. At the beginning of the Scenario, the Storyteller \nsecretly rolls a die to determine which vice he indulges in.\n1-2 Slacker: Harlequin has very little desire to work, and \nwhen he does perform a task, he does so by following exactly what he has been told. For example, if the request is \n“Deliver this letter without being seen, ” he will not even be \nseen by the recipient of the letter, without caring if they \nread it or not.\n3-4 Servant of Two Masters: Harlequin divides his \nservices between the Hunters and one of the Scenario’s \nMain NPCs. When he completes a job for the Hunters, the \nMain NPC will be notified.\n5-6 In Love: Harlequin is in love with a beautiful young \nwoman and takes advantage of every moment to be with \nher. When he leaves the Scene to perform a task, the Storyteller rolls a second die: if the result is even, Harlequin \nreturns as usual at the beginning of the next Scene. If the \nresult is odd, Harlequin returns in the middle of a Scene \nthat has already begun, making up an imaginative excuse \nto justify his delay.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Helping the Hunters as ordered by the Church, but never letting \ngo of having fun.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vtQbZTCRmsNsEkcK","name":"The Little Oni","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"bviRNnjPGv9Q6eig","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a six-year-old child and I easily get angry. \nI possess the strength and endurance of ten men. I become \nattached to the Hunters because I feel they are similar to me.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 16","positive":"I am a six-year-old child and I easily get angry. \nI possess the strength and endurance of ten men. I become \nattached to the Hunters because I feel they are similar to me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pbRwXhfUzhGrolge","name":"Gift - Blood of Oni","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Little Oni has unusual strength \nand endurance. If he acts to satisfy a whim or to get what \nhe wants, the Little Oni is considered OL Hard 7. Natural \nelements such as fire and lightning pose no danger to the \nLittle Oni, as he is completely immune to them. Each time \nhe performs a task for a Hunter, he receives 1 Whim Token.</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 16","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4U0G7UWJSqP9AYdg","name":"Gift - Tantrum","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Little Oni is a simple child, after all. \nOnce per Scene, the Storyteller may spend 1 Whim Token \nto roll for or choose one of the following problems:\n1. I want it!: The Little Oni decides that he wants an important object for himself during the Hunters’ investigation. He will use it as a toy for the rest of the Scene \nand flatly refuses to give it to anyone else.\n2. Will you take me there?: The Little Oni wants to \nvisit a place that has nothing to do with the Hunters’ \ninvestigation or a place that they are intentionally \navoiding. The Little Oni will want to be accompanied \nby a Hunter, but will also go alone if no one chooses to \ngo with him.\n3. Play with me: The Little Oni chooses a Hunter as his \nplaymate and wants their attention for the rest of the \nScene. If the Hunter does anything else, the Little Oni \nwill get in the Hunter’s way to get their attention.\n4. Sing: The Little Oni sings at the top of his lungs at the \nworst possible time, creating a terrifying dirge.\n5. Can I have a puppy?: The Little Oni wants to bring \nback an animal or monster he encountered during the \nScenario. He has a preference for large and dangerous \ncreatures.\n6. Stomping my feet: The Little Oni has become angry \nat a Hunter for some pointless reason and will refuse to \ndo anything for the rest of the Scene except annoy the \ntarget of his anger.\n17</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 16","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4FPNoDfB4w0hYtWw","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Little Oni\nInspired by the Oni Demons of Japanese \nMythology (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, a child was born with strange powers. \nFrightened, his parents took him to the temple on the near -\nby mountain to be cared for by the monks. But even they \nfound the task of raising the strange child too difficult. Oni, \nas the baby was called because of the two strange horns on \nhis forehead, possessed herculean strength, matched only by \nhis resistance to every natural element. Even the older monks \nfound it impossible to keep up with the child’s tantrums. One \nday, the famous monk Karasu Kuroi passed by the temple, \nand when he saw the little boy, he had no doubt. In his blood \nflowed the power of the Yokai. Karasu took Oni with him and \nassured the boy that he would take care of his education. But \neven for Karasu, it was impossible to handle this little force \nof nature. Oni had become attached to Karasu, and although \nthe monk had tried several times to place the child in the loving care of a family, he found Oni had followed him to Europe, \nready to wreak havoc.\nDescriptor: I am a six-year-old child and I easily get angry. \nI possess the strength and endurance of ten men. I become \nattached to the Hunters because I feel they are similar to me. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Follow the Hunters and help as I see fit / Throw \ntantrums until I get what I want.\n16\nGift - Blood of Oni: The Little Oni has unusual strength \nand endurance. If he acts to satisfy a whim or to get what \nhe wants, the Little Oni is considered OL Hard 7. Natural \nelements such as fire and lightning pose no danger to the \nLittle Oni, as he is completely immune to them. Each time \nhe performs a task for a Hunter, he receives 1 Whim Token.\nGift - Tantrum: The Little Oni is a simple child, after all. \nOnce per Scene, the Storyteller may spend 1 Whim Token \nto roll for or choose one of the following problems:\n1. I want it!: The Little Oni decides that he wants an important object for himself during the Hunters’ investigation. He will use it as a toy for the rest of the Scene \nand flatly refuses to give it to anyone else.\n2. Will you take me there?: The Little Oni wants to \nvisit a place that has nothing to do with the Hunters’ \ninvestigation or a place that they are intentionally \navoiding. The Little Oni will want to be accompanied \nby a Hunter, but will also go alone if no one chooses to \ngo with him.\n3. Play with me: The Little Oni chooses a Hunter as his \nplaymate and wants their attention for the rest of the \nScene. If the Hunter does anything else, the Little Oni \nwill get in the Hunter’s way to get their attention.\n4. Sing: The Little Oni sings at the top of his lungs at the \nworst possible time, creating a terrifying dirge.\n5. Can I have a puppy?: The Little Oni wants to bring \nback an animal or monster he encountered during the \nScenario. He has a preference for large and dangerous \ncreatures.\n6. Stomping my feet: The Little Oni has become angry \nat a Hunter for some pointless reason and will refuse to \ndo anything for the rest of the Scene except annoy the \ntarget of his anger.\n17</p>","notes":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 16","owner":"The Little Oni","source":"Dark Presence","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01ae2y6500kc4pa4","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"lost-stories-the-little-oni-16","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":16}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Little Oni\nInspired by the Oni Demons of Japanese \nMythology (Ally)\nOnce upon a time, a child was born with strange powers. \nFrightened, his parents took him to the temple on the near -\nby mountain to be cared for by the monks. But even they \nfound the task of raising the strange child too difficult. Oni, \nas the baby was called because of the two strange horns on \nhis forehead, possessed herculean strength, matched only by \nhis resistance to every natural element. Even the older monks \nfound it impossible to keep up with the child’s tantrums. One \nday, the famous monk Karasu Kuroi passed by the temple, \nand when he saw the little boy, he had no doubt. In his blood \nflowed the power of the Yokai. Karasu took Oni with him and \nassured the boy that he would take care of his education. But \neven for Karasu, it was impossible to handle this little force \nof nature. Oni had become attached to Karasu, and although \nthe monk had tried several times to place the child in the loving care of a family, he found Oni had followed him to Europe, \nready to wreak havoc.\nDescriptor: I am a six-year-old child and I easily get angry. \nI possess the strength and endurance of ten men. I become \nattached to the Hunters because I feel they are similar to me. \n3 Wounds \nOpposition Level: Easy 3\nAgenda: Follow the Hunters and help as I see fit / Throw \ntantrums until I get what I want.\n16\nGift - Blood of Oni: The Little Oni has unusual strength \nand endurance. If he acts to satisfy a whim or to get what \nhe wants, the Little Oni is considered OL Hard 7. Natural \nelements such as fire and lightning pose no danger to the \nLittle Oni, as he is completely immune to them. Each time \nhe performs a task for a Hunter, he receives 1 Whim Token.\nGift - Tantrum: The Little Oni is a simple child, after all. \nOnce per Scene, the Storyteller may spend 1 Whim Token \nto roll for or choose one of the following problems:\n1. I want it!: The Little Oni decides that he wants an important object for himself during the Hunters’ investigation. He will use it as a toy for the rest of the Scene \nand flatly refuses to give it to anyone else.\n2. Will you take me there?: The Little Oni wants to \nvisit a place that has nothing to do with the Hunters’ \ninvestigation or a place that they are intentionally \navoiding. The Little Oni will want to be accompanied \nby a Hunter, but will also go alone if no one chooses to \ngo with him.\n3. Play with me: The Little Oni chooses a Hunter as his \nplaymate and wants their attention for the rest of the \nScene. If the Hunter does anything else, the Little Oni \nwill get in the Hunter’s way to get their attention.\n4. Sing: The Little Oni sings at the top of his lungs at the \nworst possible time, creating a terrifying dirge.\n5. Can I have a puppy?: The Little Oni wants to bring \nback an animal or monster he encountered during the \nScenario. He has a preference for large and dangerous \ncreatures.\n6. Stomping my feet: The Little Oni has become angry \nat a Hunter for some pointless reason and will refuse to \ndo anything for the rest of the Scene except annoy the \ntarget of his anger.\n17</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow the Hunters and help as I see fit / Throw \ntantrums until I get what I want.\n16","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781556805433,"modifiedTime":1781556805433,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
